{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f35eb2de-6673-41bb-af9c-c21db310aa98","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"16\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key change:** The `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute tells the XAML compiler the expected type, so all `{Binding}` expressions are resolved at compile time instead of using reflection at runtime.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n1. **They're automatic** — once `x:DataType` is set, any typo like `{Binding Themee}` produces a **build error** (e.g., *\"Member 'Themee' not found on type 'SettingsViewModel'\"*).\n\n2. **Enable warnings-as-errors** (optional, for stricter enforcement) in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n   ```\n\n3. **Opting out locally** — if a binding must be dynamic (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate` with an unknown type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings for that subtree.\n\nCompiled bindings are faster (no reflection) and give you IntelliSense + compile-time safety for free.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74a7da2c-e66f-4cb8-924c-883473642c70","outputTokens":487,"requestId":"7FD0:21AE1A:5EBC51D:6788B98:69F155F6"},"id":"4afada98-4c2b-4c4d-8966-018b682fd13c","timestamp":"2026-04-